                    <h5 class="card-title">About & Mission</h5>
                    <p>
                        Welcome to Ponjo.Pastes, your secure solution for storing and sharing code
                        snippets effortlessly. We understand that developers often need a reliable
                        and simple way to manage their code, whether for personal use or
                        collaborative projects. That's why we created Ponjo.Pastes—to make code
                        snippet storage easy and secure.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        At Ponjo.Pastes, our mission is to provide a straightforward platform that
                        enables developers to store, retrieve, and share code snippets without the
                        hassle. We prioritize security and simplicity, ensuring that your data is
                        protected while remaining easily accessible. We believe that every developer
                        deserves a tool that simplifies their workflow and enhances productivity.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div id="featuresContent" class="tab-content" style="display: none;">
                    <h5 class="mb-2">Secure Storage</h5>
                    <p>
                        Your code snippets are stored with the highest security standards. We utilize
                        state-of-the-art encryption methods, including AES-256 encryption, to protect
                        your data from unauthorized access. Each snippet is securely stored in our
                        cloud infrastructure, ensuring redundancy and reliability. With Ponjo.Pastes,
                        you can rest assured that your intellectual property is safe and sound.
                    </p>
                    <h5 class="m-2">Organized & User-Friendly UI</h5>
                    <p>
                        Our intuitive design makes it easy for anyone, regardless of technical skill
                        level, to navigate and use the platform. The clean layout allows for quick
                        access to your snippets, with clearly labeled sections and search functionality.
                        Whether you're saving a quick note or managing an extensive library of code,
                        Ponjo.Pastes simplifies the process for you. We have automated syntax
                        highlighting for visually-appealing representations of your code.

                        Categorize and tag your snippets for easy retrieval. Our organization
                        features allow you to keep your code library neat and accessible, so you
                        can find what you need quickly. Utilize a powerful search function to
                        locate any code snippet in seconds. You'll spend less time searching and
                        more time coding.
                    </p>
                    <h5 class="m-2">Effortless Sharing</h5>
                    <p>
                        Sharing code snippets with colleagues or friends is a breeze. With just a
                        few clicks, you can generate secure, shareable links to your snippets,
                        allowing for instant collaboration. We are currently working on a feature
                        to allow you to set permissions on shared snippets, deciding whether
                        others can view or edit them. This makes Ponjo.Pastes an excellent tool
                        for team projects, peer reviews, or educational purposes.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Access your code snippets from anywhere, on any device. Our responsive
                        design ensures a seamless experience whether you're on a desktop, tablet,
                        or smartphone. Whether you're at your desk, on the go, or collaborating in
                        a meeting, Ponjo.Pastes ensures you can retrieve your snippets whenever
                        you need them, making it a versatile tool for modern developers.
                    </p>
                </div>
